commit 2e12f12520a0f9a723e7163720204bcc49dea307
Author: msn <msn@polaris.dev>
Date:   Tue Apr 21 00:56:54 2026 -0700

    PL: M-31 — outline JSON decode resilience (V19/V20 root cause)
    
    V19 and V20 both hit "Expecting ',' delimiter" JSON parse failures
    from the DeepSeek V3.2 outline LLM. Investigation revealed TWO
    root causes:
    
    1. PRIMARY: sweep caller was passing outline_max_tokens=800 while
       the in-module default (M-24 fix) is 2500. 5-section outlines
       with 12-20 ev_ids each need ~2000+ tokens to emit valid JSON —
       800 truncates mid-JSON, producing the "missing comma" parse
       errors (character positions 1541, 1867 — near the 800-token
       output cap).
    
       Catastrophic consequence: deterministic 3-section fallback
       loses the LLM's evidence selection. In V20, this dropped all
       48 T3 regulatory sources from the final bibliography even
       though M-28 retrieval correctly fetched them — bibliography
       went from V18's 35 cites (12 regulatory) to V20's 12 cites
       (0 regulatory), and word count fell from 2922 to 790.
    
    2. SECONDARY: DeepSeek V3.2 occasionally emits trailing commas
       before `]` / `}`. Added belt-and-suspenders lenient re-parse
       in _parse_outline. If strict json.loads fails, try once more
       with `,(\s*[}\]])` stripped. Safe transformation: well-formed
       JSON never has trailing commas, so stripping them cannot change
       the meaning of valid JSON.
    
    Changes:
    - scripts/run_honest_sweep_r3.py: outline_max_tokens 800 → 2500
    - src/polaris_graph/generator/multi_section_generator.py:
      _parse_outline now attempts lenient trailing-comma cleanup on
      strict-parse failure, then re-attempts json.loads.
    
    Tests (+6):
    - Trailing-comma lists (ev_ids / sections) → recovered
    - Well-formed JSON still parses (non-regression)
    - Truncation case still fails (proving lenient doesn't
      over-relax)
    - Lenient pass preserves semantics on valid input
    - Static guard: sweep script outline_max_tokens must be ≥2500
    
    tests_passed: 753/753 (+6 M-31)
    V21 sweep to follow after Codex code audit.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

